---
import CaseStudy from "@/layouts/case-study.astro"
import { getProject } from "@/data/projects"

const project = getProject("ncga-template-system")!
---

<CaseStudy
  project={project}
  title="NCGA Reusable Template System"
  description="A draft case study about reusable templates and visual standards for recurring public-sector communications."
>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    I built reusable standards and templates for recurring legislative
    materials at the North Carolina General Assembly, so teams could produce
    complex public-sector communications with more consistency and less
    rework across print and digital channels.
  </p>

  <h2>Problem</h2>
  <p>
    Recurring legislative materials needed a more consistent structure so teams
    could produce accurate print and digital communications without rebuilding
    the same decisions each cycle.
  </p>

  <h2>Role</h2>
  <p>
    Graphic and production designer at the North Carolina General Assembly. I
    handled layout systems, visual standards, production workflows, and
    public-sector communication needs.
  </p>

  <h2>Next Draft Pass</h2>
  <p>
    The next pass should add representative artifacts, define the template
    system’s parts, and describe production improvements with only verifiable
    claims.
  </p>
</CaseStudy>
